result.name: Ootoya

reviews.text:
Originated from Japan.  Most of the meat and fish are imported there. The Japanese chief chef works well to maintain a quality standard as equally good as in Japan. Offers various kind of meal set and a la cart. Lunch and dinner menu are basically the same but there are skewers and sashimi available at dinner time. Price point is not low but very fair for what you get.

Peak hours always got queue and reservation not accepted. So better go ahead or after the crowd.  Ultimately, there are many restaurants in the building as backup. 😅

This is my first time in this shop, usually I go to Kowloon side branch.  There is not much people during 12 o clock noon time, only 4 or 5 tables are occupied.  They do have special price lunch menu.  And they are around 80 dollars.  I have tried the mini size salmon rice and cold soba.  They are come in as a lunch set.  Surprisingly,  the taste is better than the other branches I tried before.  And the place is quite spacious.  I do enjoy my lunch here today.  5 🌟!!!
Good location, good services and good price ~
Good service and the side dishes are the best among all branches, I like this one greatly!
The food was sub par, the air con was broken, the toilet was out of order and the tables were close to.each other. Terrible experience.
